        -: 3689:/*
        -: 3690: * anova() : sequential (Type-I) ANOVA table for a linear model, returned in
        -: 3691: *           the same shape as aov() in this module, OR an F-test comparison
        -: 3692: *           of two or more nested models (R's anova(m1, m2, ...) generic).
        -: 3693: *
        -: 3694: *   my $tab = anova(\%data, 'yield ~ ctrl');            # one model  -> HashRef
        -: 3695: *   my $tab = anova(\%data, 'len ~ supp * dose');       # one model  -> HashRef
        -: 3696: *   my $cmp = anova(\%data, 'y ~ a', 'y ~ a + b');      # 2+ models  -> ArrayRef
        -: 3697: *
        -: 3698: * ---- single-model form (one formula) --------------------------------------
        -: 3699: * Input mirrors aov(): a Hash-of-Arrays (\%h, columns) or Array-of-Hashes
        -: 3700: * (\@a, rows), plus a formula string 'response ~ rhs'. The RHS understands
        -: 3701: * '+', ':' (interaction) and '*' (factorial expansion: a*b -> a + b + a:b,
        -: 3702: * a*b*c -> a + b + c + a:b + a:c + b:c + a:b:c). Bare string columns are
        -: 3703: * treated as factors and treatment-coded (first level = reference); numeric
        -: 3704: * columns and I(x^2) enter as single regressors. Interactions form the
        -: 3705: * product of their factors' coded columns, so factor:factor uses
        -: 3706: * (la-1)*(lb-1) columns exactly as R's treatment contrasts do.
        -: 3707: *
        -: 3708: * The model is fit sequentially by Householder QR (apply_householder_aov)
        -: 3709: * and the model SS is decomposed term by term, in formula order (Type I).
        -: 3710: * Collinear / rank-deficient terms gracefully receive 0 df and 0 Sum Sq.
        -: 3711: * Rows with any missing / non-numeric response or predictor are dropped
        -: 3712: * listwise (R's default na.omit).
        -: 3713: *
        -: 3714: * Returns a HashRef keyed by term name (plus "Residuals"); each value is a
        -: 3715: * nested hash using R's column names:
        -: 3716: *     term        => { Df, "Sum Sq", "Mean Sq", "F value", "Pr(>F)" }
        -: 3717: *     Residuals   => { Df, "Sum Sq", "Mean Sq" }
        -: 3718: * "Mean Sq"/"F value"/"Pr(>F)" are omitted where undefined (0-df terms; the
        -: 3719: * Residuals row never carries an F test), matching aov()'s output.
        -: 3720: *
        -: 3721: * ---- model-comparison form (two or more formulas) -------------------------
        -: 3722: * anova(\%data, 'y ~ a', 'y ~ a + b', ...) fits every model and returns an
        -: 3723: * ArrayRef with one HashRef per model, in the order supplied, mirroring R's
        -: 3724: * anova(m1, m2, ...) table (columns Res.Df, RSS, Df, Sum of Sq, F, Pr(>F)):
        -: 3725: *     [ { "Res.Df", "RSS", formula },
        -: 3726: *       { "Res.Df", "RSS", "Df", "Sum of Sq", "F", "Pr(>F)", formula }, ... ]
        -: 3727: * The first row carries no comparison stats (nothing precedes it). For each
        -: 3728: * later row: Df = drop in residual df from the previous model, "Sum of Sq" =
        -: 3729: * drop in RSS, and F = ("Sum of Sq"/Df) / scale, where scale is the residual
        -: 3730: * mean square of the *largest* model in the set (smallest residual df) --
        -: 3731: * the common denominator R uses for the whole table. "F"/"Pr(>F)" are omitted
        -: 3732: * for any row whose Df is not positive (non-nested / equal-size steps).
        -: 3733: *
        -: 3734: * All models are fit on ONE shared row set: completeness is evaluated
        -: 3735: * listwise over the UNION of every response and predictor across every
        -: 3736: * formula, so the fits are always mutually comparable (unlike R, which fits
        -: 3737: * each model on its own na.omit and then errors if the sizes disagree).
        -: 3738: *
        -: 3739: * This form performs the F-test only. R's Chisq/LRT variant would need a
        -: 3740: * chi-square CDF; it can be layered on later behind a test option.
        -: 3741: *
        -: 3742: * Depends on: parse_formula(), apply_householder_aov(), pf(),
        -: 3743: * evaluate_term(), is_column_categorical(), get_data_string_alloc().
        -: 3744: */
