        -: 4991:
        -: 4992:# Row-level de-duplication core for drop_duplicates().  The Perl wrapper
        -: 4993:# validates the frame, rejects HoH, and resolves `subset` into an ordered
        -: 4994:# list of column identifiers (integer positions for AoA, names for AoH/HoA).
        -: 4995:#   shape: 1 = AoH, 3 = AoA, 4 = HoA
        -: 4996:#   subset: arrayref of the columns whose cells define a row's identity
        -: 4997:#   keep:  1 = first occurrence, -1 = last occurrence, 0 = drop every dup
        -: 4998:# AoA/AoH survivors reuse the original row refs (cells shared, like dropna);
        -: 4999:# HoA rebuilds every column sliced to the surviving row positions.
        -: 5000:SV *
        -: 5001:_drop_dups_core(df, shape, subset, keep)
        -: 5002:	SV *df
        -: 5003:	IV shape
        -: 5004:	SV *subset
